		"body": "<!--\r\n\r\nBefore contributing, please read the contribution guidelines: https://github.com/laurent22/joplin/blob/dev/readme/dev/index.md\r\n\r\nIf this is a Google Summer of Code pull request, please read the [GSoC pull request guidelines](https://github.com/joplin/gsoc/blob/master/pull_request_guidelines.md).\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n**Pull request title**: Please prefix the title with the platform you are targetting.\r\n\r\nHere are some examples of good titles:\r\n\r\n- Desktop: Resolves #123: Added new setting to change font\r\n- Mobile, Desktop: Fixes #456: Fixed config screen error\r\n- All: Resolves #777: Made synchronisation faster\r\n\r\nAnd here's an explanation of the title format:\r\n\r\n- \"Desktop\" for the Windows/macOS/Linux app (Electron app)\r\n- \"Mobile\" for the mobile app (or \"Android\" / \"iOS\" if the pull request only applies to one of the mobile platforms)\r\n- \"CLI\" for the CLI app\r\n\r\nIf it's two platforms, separate them with commas - \"Desktop, Mobile\" or if it's for all platforms, prefix with \"All\".\r\n\r\nIf it's not related to any platform (such as a translation, change to the documentation, etc.), simply don't add a platform.\r\n\r\nThen please append the issue that you've addressed or fixed. Use \"Resolves #123\" for new features or improvements and \"Fixes #123\" for bug fixes.\r\n\r\n-->\r\n\r\n\r\n# CLI: Resolves #14666 : Fix `joplin use /` to Navigate to Root\r\n\r\n## Problem\r\n\r\nCurrently, running joplin use / in the CLI returns an error Cannot find \"/\" because the string / is passed directly to loadItem, which expects a physical folder name.\r\n\r\nWhile the underlying data model doesn't have a \"root notebook\" entity, the CLI recognizes a root-level namespace (as seen with joplin ls /). Users currently have no way to navigate back to this top-level context once they have \"used\" a specific notebook, making it difficult to create new top-level notebooks or list all notebooks without restarting the CLI.\r\n\r\n## Solution\r\nThis PR allows joplin use / to act as a command to clear the current folder context and return to the root.\r\n\r\ncommand-use.ts: Added an early return check. If the input is /, it calls switchCurrentFolder(null) to clear the active folder state.\r\n\r\nBaseApplication.ts: Updated switchCurrentFolder to ensure that when a null value is passed, currentFolder_ is explicitly set to null instead of an empty object {}. This ensures that command-ls and other context-aware commands correctly detect that the user is at the root.\r\n\r\n\r\n## To verify the fix, perform the following steps in the CLI:\r\n\r\n1. Switch to a notebook: joplin use \"Notebook 1\"\r\n2. Verify context: Run joplin ls. It should show notes/folders inside \"Notebook 1\".\r\n3. Navigate to root: Run joplin use /.\r\n4. Verify root context: Run a plain joplin ls (without arguments). It should now list all top-level notebooks, confirming the context has successfully switched back to root.\r\n\r\n## Automated Test Results\r\n\r\nAll 11 CLI integration tests pass:\r\n\r\n```\r\nPASS app/cli-integration-tests.test.js (40.605 s)\r\n  cli-integration-tests\r\n    ✓ should run command \"version\" without crashing (753 ms)\r\n    ✓ should run command \"help\" without crashing (957 ms)\r\n    ✓ should support the 'ls' command (2772 ms)\r\n    ✓ should support the 'mv' command (6111 ms)\r\n    ✓ should support the 'use' command (4793 ms)\r\n    ✓ should support creating and removing folders (2742 ms)\r\n    ✓ should support creating and removing notes (4921 ms)\r\n    ✓ should support listing the contents of notes (2664 ms)\r\n    ✓ should support changing settings with config (1964 ms)\r\n    ✓ should support 'use /' to return to root (4682 ms)\r\n    ✓ should support copying folders with cp (3407 ms)\r\n\r\nTests: 11 passed, 11 total\r\n```\r\n",
